Package: emacs28-lucid
Architecture: any
Depends: emacs28-bin-common (= ${binary:Version}), ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Provides: emacs28, emacsen, editor, info-browser, mail-reader, news-reader
Suggests: emacs28-common-non-dfsg
Conflicts: emacs28-no-native-comp-lucid,
  emacs28, emacs28-nox, emacs28-common (<< 2:20150222+emacs-pretest-24.0.05-15849-g3f006e1-1)
Replaces: emacs28, emacs28-nox
Description: GNU Emacs editor (with Lucid GUI support)
 GNU Emacs is the extensible self-documenting text editor.  This
 package contains a version of Emacs with support for a graphical user
 interface based on the Lucid toolkit (instead of the GTK+ interface
 provided by the emacs28 package).  Until some known GTK+
 problems are fixed, this version may help avoid crashing Emacs during
 an emacsclient disconnect.  See
 https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=567934 and
 https://bugzilla.gnome.org/show_bug.cgi?id=85715 for more
 information.

